PagingResponseMetadata.documentation: Fields for sorting and paging through lists

ResourceAuthorization.documentation: Authorization object for resource. Locale-Specific condition override Locale-Agnostic conditions.

SearchPagingResponseMetadata.documentation: Fields for sorting and paging through search results

adminGroup.documentation: Group name in LDAP for users who can change directory settings

conditionValue.documentation: Value for authorization condition, null to remove

configuration.documentation: A map to allow enabling features or storing custom configuration at a directory level

continuationKey.documentation: The continuation key used to page through results

continuationMarker.documentation: The continuation marker is a Base64 encoded key which is used to page through results

count.documentation: The number of entities returned in the given result

createdBy.documentation: Name of the user creating the item

cti.documentation: CTI defined in https://cti.amazon.com/ which will receive tickets about items in the directory

dateUpdated.documentation: The date the object was last updated

directoryName.documentation: Directory name, used to determine identifier via normalization

displayOrder.documentation: Display order determines the order of directory fields on Directories Authoring UI. Display order only allows integer value greater than or equal to 0, where 0 means not set for ordering.

editorGroup.documentation: Group name in LDAP for users who can add items to a directory

fieldDescription.documentation: Allows author to put description details for this directory field.

friendlyName.documentation: Allows author to specify a friendly name for this directory field.

includeItemTags.documentation: Whether to embed the ItemTag objects in each Tag object returned

includeResourceAuthorization.documentation: Whether to include resource's authorization in response

internalVersion.documentation: The records version number used for concurrency checks

itemId.documentation: Identifies an item that is being requested

itemName.documentation: Item name, i.e., title; used to determine identifier via normalization

itemTargetStatus.documentation: The status for an item target (Whether an item version is published to the target or the entire item is deleted)

lastUpdatedBy.documentation: Name of the user updating the item

limit.documentation: The number of entities to return per page in a list

locale.documentation: Locale for directories and items, e.g. en_US or de_DE

location.documentation: This is the canonical URL for the item (location of an item). This field is only populated in the response of a redirect URL mapping.

numImpressions.documentation: The number of times the item has been viewed

orderBy.documentation: The name of the field on which to order

primaryOwner.documentation: Username in LDAP who owns the directory (e.g. for escalations)

published.documentation: Whether the item is published, i.e., visible on the site

rangeOperator.documentation: The comparison operator to use on the range value

reviewerGroup.documentation: Group name in LDAP for users who can approve or deny workflows which act upon items in a directory

searchValueType.documentation: The data type of the search value

sortAscending.documentation: Sort in ascending order if true; otherwise, descending order

sortOrder.documentation: The comparison operator to use on the range value

sortOrderRank.documentation: Sort order rank determines the order in which sort order field is constructed, e.g. for a field Location#EventDate, Location rank is 1 and EventDate rank is 2

status.documentation: Current status of a record, eg: Item, TagNamespace, ItemTag, etc

tagMeta.documentation: Used to store additional information about tags

tagNamespaceType.documentation: Tag namespace type, eg: GLOBAL or LOCAL

urlFormat.documentation: URL format defined on the directory which is used to create default item URL

urlMappingType.documentation: Type of URL mapping (analogous to Http status code)
